HEY GUYS
I KNOW THAT MY ENTRIES HAVE BEEN FEW AND FAR BETWEEN BUT IM WORKING ON MY NINTH STRAIGHT DAY OFF CLASS INCLUDING SAT AND SUN SO...  BUT TO BEGIN I HAVE A KIND OF SAD NOTE MY FRIEND JACKY'S UNCLE PASTED AWAY YESTERDAY SO PLEASE PRAY FOR THE KEMP FAMILY.  
NOW RIGHT SO YESTERDAY WHICH STARTED OFF PRETTY GOOD, WE WERE IN THE THEATRE DOING RIGGING STUFF WHICH I THINK IS THE COOLEST THING EVER.  WE WERE USING A PIN RAIL FLY SYSTEM WHICH IS SORT OF LIKE THE FLY SYSTEM IN SCHOOL FOR THOSE OF YOU THEATRE FOLK, EXCEPT THAT ITS LIKE "OLD SCHOOL" SO SAND BAG WEIGHTS, AND SIX-TEN PEOPLE FOR ONE FLY BAR IT WAS SO AWSOME.  BUT THEN WE WENT DOWNSTAIRS TO THE SCENE SHOP,  IM ON CARPENTRY ROTATION, AND THAT SUCKED.  THE CARPENTERS ARE TWO WEEKS BEHIND ON BUILDING THE CURRENT SHOW, THREE SISTERS, THATS FIRST OF ALL, SECONDLY WE CUT WINDOWS OUT OF 2 SHEETS OF 3/4 INCH PLY WHICH IS THICK SO THE WINDOWS ARENT LEVEL... THUS THE FRESHMAN HAD TO SAND DOWN THE WINDOWS TO MAKE THEM LEVEL... ERGO 6 FRESHMAN INHALING SAWDUST FOR 6 HRS... NOT GOOD.  I AM SO SICK TODAY I FEEL LIKE I HAVD A LUMP OF SAWDUST IN MY LUNGS ISNT THAT LOVELY.  AND ASIDE FROM THAT WE STILL HAVE ANOTHER WINDOW TO BUILD OUT OF THE SAME CRAP... GRRRR. AND NOW HAVING SAID THAT, IM THINKING ABOUT CHANGING MY MAJOR, IM MEAN STILL BE A DT CAUSE I LOVE IT BUT IM NOT SURE IF I WANT TO BE A LIGHTING DESIGNER ANYMORE... IM REALLY TORN BETWEEN THAT AND TECHNICAL DIRECTION... FOR THOSE OF YOU WHO DONT REALLY KNOW THE DIFFERENCE IT LIKE ELECTRICS V. CARPENTRY... I LOVE THEM BOTH.  I WANT TO DOUBLE MAJOR BECAUSE I REALLY WANT TO DO BOTH BUT YOUR NOT ALLOWED TO BECAUSE LEAVE IT TO ME TO PICK THE TWO HARDEST MAJORS IN THE PROGRAM... SO THE BOARD OF STUDY WONT AND CANT LET ANY STUDENT DOUBLE MAJOR IN THOSE TO FEILDS AND THOSE R THE ONLY ONES THAT YOU CANT.  ALSO JUST TO LET YOU KNOW THAT I REALLY AM CRAZY, OVER WINTER BREAK... WHICH FOR ME IS THE MONTH OF DECEMBER IM TAKING A 4 WEEK LIBERAL STUDIES COURSE... BUT THATS TECHNICALLY TO GET IT OUT OF THE WAY FOR JUNIOR/SENIOR YEAR.  
IN OTHER NEWS I MAY BE ON RUNNING CREW FOR THE UP COMMING SHOW WHICH MEANS I REALLY WONT BE HOME FOR LIKE THREE WEEKS AND YEA UNFORTUNATELY THAT MEANS IM NOT COMMING HOME FOR HALLOWSEEN WEEKEND... SRY GUYS
BUT NOW THAT IVE GONE ON FOR A WHILE I HAVE TO GO  I HAVE CLASS IN 20 MIN AND I WANT TO BE KIND OF EARLY SO I CAN GET COFFEE  SO ILL TALK TO YOU GUYS SOON... TELL PPLE I SAY HI... ESP GURLEY AND COULTER AND ILL SEE YOU SOON
LATER DAYS... YES MELISSA THE WEEKENDERS
KATE

The only part that wasnt good was that my parents were commung up at 1030 so I had to wake up early to pack so I got like 3 hrs of sleep and my eyes were really blood shot.  Umm so home was fun, I saw melissa Im glad you lke the shirt honey, and I hung out with my friend Cat sat night, That was fun we shot some pool, went to cappichino bar, nd then hung out on her stoop.  I get home at like 2.  Sunday was un eventful, It was mostly homework and sleep, and movies... resting up for the next couple of weeks I have class from 3-10.. production, and we have ad load in and strike this weekend sat and sun.  But so going home back to campus last night was fun, I was drinking coffee and i was way to hyper and ended up doing like 80 on the hutch, my mom was in the back like kate? how fast r u goin? I was like 65  don't worry, that was the most fun Ive had driving in a ling time.  Ummm lets see I think thats it, I hope every ones ok and when yoiu get a chance e mail me and we can have a more one on one convo... umm and if ne one knows sarah rebecca gaglio tell her i said hi and that she should email me... shes a fresh.  Pk ne way i have to go i have class in an hr so i just kinda want to chill b4 then Ill talk to you guys soon
Kate

Hey Guys, 

For starters....GLBT & straight alliance thing, if u dont care scroll down.  This is a call for a nation-wide boycott in the traditions of Gandhi and Dr. Martin Luther King. They are asking all GLBT Americans & their Straight Allies to "drop out" of the United States economy for one day to demonstrate that we are vital & important members of our communities with significant economic presence. There are three elements to the boycott: No Work, No Purchases and No Cell Phones.
On February 24, 2004, the President of the United States declared war on gay/bisexual/transgendered Americans when he decided to support a Constitutional Amendment banning Same-Sex Marriage denying gay & lesbians over 1000 rights & responsibilities that all other Americans currently enjoy.
In addition, the Congress & State Legislatures have refused numerous attempts to pass employment non-discrimination laws. The discriminatory Don't Ask Don't Tell policy continues to make a mockery of the service of lesbian & gay service people, when other democracies (i.e. Great Britain) allow gays to serve in the military.
GLBT citizens pay taxes everyday to support our government & society, just like heterosexual citizens. As such, they will no longer be treated as second-class citizens without the full protection of the law in employment non-discrimination or legal status in marriage, adoption or other rights. They should be able to serve our country with distinction without fear of discharge.
Gay people do not choose to be gay -- who would logically choose to be despised by the majority. They do not choose to be homosexual any more than straights decide to be heterosexual. Left-handed people do not choose to be different than the right-handed majority -- they just are.
So in conclusion its like a silent protest. Like Rosa Parks did when they boycotted the buses. All you have to do it not use your cell phone, buy anything, & go to work. Just hang out. Its that easy. You dont have to be a gay male or a lesbian female to do this. If you believe that gays & lesbians should have the same rights as straight people then you should participate on October 8th.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Hey eveyone... i hope everyone is having a great end of the summer...and dont sound to depressed that your going back to school, senior year was alot of fun and it goes really quickly so have fun with it... and for thoes of you who arent seniors...work as hard as you can because it worth it in the end, it make life eaiser down the road.  So anyway... lastnight was the GET LEID party, hosted by the GLBTU   gay lesbian bisexual transgender unity... it was interesting, the most fun was watching the gay guys dance, they had some good moves. SO i guess that was good even tho clarissa wasnt there.  After about an hr, all the dt's left we had our own party called "freshman roundup" that was interesting, everyone was drunk except me and like two other people, one of the guys in my class had something like 24 beers and some shots and was so sick... it was actually kind of funny, cause we had to all get up fpr an 830 class. now im not saying that when you get to college or even now you should go and get drunk, but im not saying not to...just what ever you do please do it responsibly, be careful. Im comming home tomorrow so if anyones around and wants to chill for alittle while just give me a call.  
OK  im going back to sleep for a little while  im done  with class for the day
talk to you soon
kate

My suiet mates are pretty cool, last night we sat outside in the quad and as pple walked by we asked then to be out friends... it was interesting.  Ok I have to go I have a meeting in ten minutes...I'll wright again soon.
Kate

ahhhh....im so board....im dying i feel like a prisoner i cant go anywhere cuz theres n place to go...
